{"questionId":"27901","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A particle moves such that its velocity, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math> metres per second, at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> seconds,&nbsp;is given by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>t</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find an expression for the acceleration of the particle.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to use product rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27901","referenceCode":"22N.1.AHL.TZ0.14a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find an expression for the acceleration of the particle.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.9—Differentiating standard functions and derivative rules","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.13—Kinematic problems"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}